    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Answer user questions hands-free\n\n**Pattern:** Chatbot Responder · **Level:** Core · **Trigger:** Chat\n\n## What it does\nAnswer user questions hands-free. It responds live to chat messages.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual task automation is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nWhen Chat Message Received → Required Fields Present? → Classify with AI → Store as Question → Reunite Branches → Tag Pipeline Metadata → Send Summary to Slack\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to chatbot responder without manual effort\n- Anyone automating task automation in ai\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Improves response time\n- Scales without extra headcount\n- Standardizes the process every time\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: Google OAuth2 / service account; OpenAI API key; Slack OAuth2.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.",
        "width": 480,
        "height": 900
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -830,
        80
      ],
      "id": "176de0a1-8aee-86dc-4a25-7874d11cef7b",
      "name": "📘 Workflow Overview"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 3
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -230,
        -500
      ],
      "id": "6d0f3f7d-e3ed-3f6c-9973-f04883e4f5b6",
      "name": "🛟 Error handling & retries"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🤖 AI cluster\n\nPurple nodes form one AI unit: the root node orchestrates, sub-nodes plug in via typed ports (model / memory / tools / parser). Swap the chat model without rewiring anything else. Costs scale with tokens — keep prompts lean and cap iterations.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 6
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        190,
        -500
      ],
      "id": "6f0d61fb-2e35-1dda-595c-db0f43f0a516",
      "name": "🤖 AI cluster"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your task automation process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 4
      },
